parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the backup camera can increase the risk of accidents or injuries when reversing, as the driver may not have a clear view of the surroundings.
symptoms: The backup camera display turns on and off
the camera image is distorted or unclear
the camera fails to turn on at all
the camera display is intermittent.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintentional deployment of the vehicle awning while in motion can cause a distraction to the driver, increase the risk of accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The awning deploys suddenly while driving
the awning deploys without warning
the awning does not retract properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent disconnection of the Bluetooth system can cause a distraction to the driver, taking their eyes off the road and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The Bluetooth connection drops frequently
the phone or navigation system disconnects from the vehicle's system
the system requires repeated reconnections
the driver is forced to take their eyes off the road to remake the connection.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to hesitate or fail to shift into gear, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially in city traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to go into gear when placed in DRIVE
shifts extremely hard into first gear
continues to shift with a hard thump into sequential gears
and may cause the vehicle to lose traction or control in snowy conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in receiving the necessary parts for the recall repair can leave the vehicle in an unsafe condition, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but parts are not available
and the manufacturer has exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unwanted engine braking can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially in snowy conditions.
symptoms: The transaxle downshifts whenever the accelerator pedal is released and the vehicle gains speed
causing unwanted engine braking
loss of traction
and loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The power window malfunction can cause physical harm or injury to the driver or occupants, especially when the window gets stuck in an upward position, trapping the head or neck.
symptoms: The power window moves in the opposite direction of the intended command
getting stuck in an upward position
trapping the head or neck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the infotainment system can compromise safety features, such as the backup camera, navigation, and telematic systems, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The radio system
navigation
and backup camera intermittently fail or malfunction while driving
resulting in the loss of critical safety features.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to use the second-row seat belts can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident, compromising the safety of passengers.
symptoms: The second-row seat belts remain in a locked position
do not pull out
and are inoperable
making it impossible to use them.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Missing LATCH Anchors for Car Seat
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence of LATCH anchors can make it difficult or impossible to properly install a car seat, increasing the risk of injury or death to children in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The vehicle is missing LATCH anchors for car seat installation.
